text: Tetuin is a flavone. It is a type of flavonoid. It is the 6-O-glucoside of baicalein. It can be isolated from the seeds of Oroxylum indicum, the Indian trumpetflower,Mehta C. R. and Mehta T. P., 1959 Journal of the Indian Chemical Society 36:468 known as टेटु tetu in Marathi. ==References== Category:Organic compounds
title: Tetuin
